The IMF announced a steep downgrade to 3.6% to its global growth forecast for this year as a result of the war in Ukraine and accelerated inflation in many countries, as well as other factors. With no end in sight for the war, what could be done to improve the global economic outlook? How can inflation be managed? And how can we better respond to global shocks and uncertainty? To discuss these issues and more, we've invited Steven Barnett, senior resident representative in China of the International Monetary Fund.